        <h2><span class="highlight">Professional Services Marketing</span> — Questions <span class="highlight">Answered</span></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d1">
          <summary>How much does professional services marketing cost in Singapore?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Most professional services firms in Singapore invest between $2,500 and $10,000 per month on marketing, depending on practice size, number of partners, and competitiveness of the practice area. A solo property agent or independent advisor may start lower, while a multi-partner law or accounting firm competing on high-value matters invests more. Engagements typically cover website, SEO, paid search, content, and social — coordinated under one strategy.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d2">
          <summary>Do you understand the advertising compliance rules for my profession?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Legal advertising in Singapore is governed by the Legal Profession (Professional Conduct) Rules, financial advisory marketing must comply with MAS guidelines, and real estate promotions are subject to Council for Estate Agencies (CEA) rules. We build campaigns that generate qualified leads without crossing these regulatory lines — a constraint generic agencies routinely get wrong.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d3">
          <summary>Which marketing channels work best for professional services firms?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Google Search captures high-intent prospects actively looking for a lawyer, accountant, agent, or advisor. SEO and a credibility-led website convert that research into enquiries. Thought-leadership content and LinkedIn build authority for B2B and high-value work, while Google Ads captures urgent, transactional searches. The right mix depends on whether you serve consumers or businesses, and on your practice area.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d1">
          <summary>How long before marketing generates new client enquiries?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Paid search can generate enquiries within the first weeks. SEO and content typically take 3–6 months to build sustainable organic visibility for competitive practice-area terms. Most professional services clients see a meaningful lift in qualified enquiries within the first 60–90 days of a coordinated campaign, with authority and rankings compounding over time.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d2">
          <summary>Do you work with law firms, accounting firms, property agents, and financial advisors?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes — those four are our core professional services verticals, each with its own dedicated marketing approach. We also work with consultancies, corporate secretarial firms, and other advisory practices. Every engagement is built around the trust-and-credibility purchase that defines professional services, and around the specific compliance regime that governs your profession.</p></div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


